  "prompt": "What are the most intelligent species on Earth other than human beings?",
  "response": "Several species are known for their high levels of intelligence, aside from humans. Some of the most intelligent include:\n\n1. **Dolphins**: They exhibit complex problem-solving skills, advanced communication abilities, and social structures.\n2. **Great Apes**: This group includes chimpanzees, bonobos, gorillas, and orangutans. They have demonstrated tool use, self-awareness, and complex social behaviors.\n3. **Elephants**: Known for their memory, empathy, and social complexity, elephants also show problem-solving skills and self-awareness.\n4. **Cephalopods**: Octopuses, cuttlefish, and squid have remarkable problem-solving abilities, can navigate mazes, and use tools.\n5. **Corvids**: Birds like crows, ravens, and magpies are known for their problem-solving skills, use of tools, and complex social behaviors.\n6. **Dogs**: Domestic dogs have been shown to understand human commands, exhibit social intelligence, and can learn and perform complex tasks.\n7. **Parrots**: Known for their ability to mimic human speech, they also demonstrate problem-solving skills and social behaviors.\n\nThese species have shown various forms of intelligence in their ability to solve problems, communicate, use tools, and interact socially.",
